 (state of not caring about other people's feelings) of decisions to risk disgust may have been (stated that something is much bigger, worse, etc., than it really is) by 
 basing the bring outation of utility functions on a range of payoffs going along with/matching up to just 10 ha. This in itself would not have been a major concern but for 
 the idea (you think is true) that decisions are independent of the scale of the problem. 
 Given that income (quality of changing over time or at different places) is positively related to crop area this idea (you think is true) is silly. In Thornton's study all decisions are made on the basis of 
 a small-scale problem in which risk is bound to be of minor importance. 
 Zacharias and Grube (1984) talked to/looked at this issue in their application of 
